Portugal is set to build the world's largest solar energy power station in Moura, with 350,000 solar panels covering 114 hectares.
The project, overseen by Amper Central Solar, will produce 62 megawatts and create 240 permanent jobs in Alentejo.
Meanwhile, a Dutch team won a solar-powered car race in Australia, showcasing the potential of solar energy.
In the Philippines, a solar power project aims to provide electricity to rural households and essential facilities.
Taiwan is also making strides in solar energy development, with a goal to become a top-five solar energy firm by 2008.
